{'book': {'publisher': 'OECD Publications and Information Centre [distributor]', 'synopsis': 'OECD governments have declared that enterprises operating in their territory but controlled by nationals of another Member country should be treated no less favorably than domestic enterprises -- in other words, they should be accorded national treatment. The steps already taken in this direction by Member countries have improved the climate for international investment. This book provides a comprehensive explanation of the scope and nature of the OECD National Treatment instrument which provides a multilateral framework for promoting further progress towards liberal international investment policies.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/92/37/9789264139237.jpg', 'title_long': 'National treatment for foreign-controlled enterprises', 'dimensions': 'Weight: 0.65477291814 Pounds', 'dimensions_structured': {'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.65477291814}}, 'pages': 185, 'date_published': '1993', 'subjects': ['Business & Money', 'Economics'], 'authors': ['unknown author'], 'title': 'National treatment for foreign-controlled enterprises', 'isbn13': '9789264139237', 'msrp': 209.26, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '9264139230', 'isbn10': '9264139230'}}